<div class='main-content' id='home-index'>

	<section class='odd'>
		<div class='container'>
			<div class='row-wrapper' id='overview'>
				<div class='row'>

					<div class='col-xs-6 col-md-8'>
						<div class='desc'>
							<h1>Overview</h1>
							<p><i>
								Iris Dynamics produces precision motion control systems that are transforming how people
								interact with all types of machines.
							</i></p>
							<p>
								Our patent-pending technology provides haptic feedback and control loading technology
								at a significantly lower cost than previously available. The core technology creates a
								realistic operating experience and is ideally suited for flight simulation, as well as
								remote operation applications in aerospace equipment, submersibles, terrestrial vehicles and
								heavy machinery.
							</p>

							<div class='col-md-6 desc nospace'>
								<h3> Advantages </h3>
								<ul>
									<li>Cost effective, simple upgrade to existing simulation systems</li>
									<li>Low latency, anti-cogging and virtually frictionless operation provides smooth real-time response</li>
									<li>A single moving part increases reliability and lowers maintenance costs</li>
									<li>Accurate force modeling enhances realism and reduces training costs</li>
									<li>Better simulator training improves safety and reduces equipment operating costs</li>
									<li>Lowers CO2 emissions and energy costs by reducing equipment operating time</li>
								</ul>
							</div>

							<div class='col-md-6 desc nospace'>
								<h3> Applications </h3>
								<ul>
									<li>Flight Training and Simulation</li>
									<li>Remote-Controlled Subsea/Submersible Devices</li>
									<li>Remotely Piloted Aircraft Systems</li>
									<li>Tele-Robotics</li>
									<li>Remotely Operated Vehicles (ROVs)</li>
									<li>Heavy Equipment</li>
									<li>Specialized Simulation Systems</li>
								</ul>
							</div>

						</div>
					</div>
					<div class='col-xs-6 col-md-4'>
						<div class='image-hook'>
							<%= image_tag 'iris-tech-3-trans.png', Class: 'pull-right tech-image' %>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class='sec-break' id='our-tech-heading'>
		<h1 class='squid-white'>EmZ Technology</h1>
		<%= image_tag '350-px-slides/iStock_000015463791_Medium.jpg', class: 'sec-image' %>
	</section>

	<section class='even'>
		<div class='container'>
			<div class='row-wrapper' id='our-tech'>
				<div class='row'>

					<div class='col-md-12 desc'>
						<h2>EmZ Technology</h2>
							<h3>What is EmZ Electro-Mechanical Impedance Technology and How Does It Work?</h3>
					</div>

					<div class='col-md-6'>
						<span>
							<%= image_tag 'wireframe-coil-shaft.png', class: 'pull-right tech-image' %>
						</span>
						<div class='desc'>
							<p>
							IRIS Dynamics has developed an innovative technology which employs electromagnetic force to vary
							the mechanical impedance of actuators. Ideal for simulation systems where control loading and
							haptic feel is essential for realistic training, EmZ Technology is applicable to broad classes of
							motion control where human operators require precision control of machines.
							</p>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class='col-md-6'>
						<span>
							<%= image_tag 'wireframe-coil.png', class: 'pull-right tech-image' %>
						</span>
						<div class='desc'>
							<p>
							EmZ Technology uses patent-pending electromagnetic design and software algorithms to replace
							complex mechanical gears, pulleys, pneumatic and/or hydraulic systems with many moving parts.
							This dramatically increases motion fidelity and minimizes initial and on-going maintenance costs.
							</p>
						</div>
					</div>


					<div class='desc col-md-12'>
						<div class='col-xs-4'>
							<%= image_tag 'iris_words.jpg', class: 'no-pad tech-image' %>
						</div>
						<div class='col-xs-8'>
							<blockquote class='tech-quote'>
								<h4><i>
									"Iris Dynamics' solution is a mechanically simple design with a single moving part, which translates
									to reduced costs, higher reliability, and operation in challenging environments. It feels natural
									and real like flying an actual aircraft."
								</i></h4>
							</blockquote>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class='col-md-12 desc'>
						<p>
							This new class of tactile motion control systems with force feedback is adaptable and scalable,
							with applications in a wide variety of industries.
							Iris Dynamics is currently working on various tactile teleoperation projects.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

